link:labelLink.link:label: Counterparty ANZSIC2006 Division
This dimension categorises the reported information according to the ANZSIC division classification of the counterparty to the transaction that gave rise to the reported information.
Agric Forestry Fishing

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC 2006 classification in Division A (Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "01" to "05". The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classification and code range was Division A 0100 - 0499.
Arts Recreation Other

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC 2006 classification in Division R (Arts and Recreation) or S (Other Services) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "89" or higher. The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classification and code range was Division P (Cultural and Recreational Services) and Q (Personal and Other Services) 9100 - 9799.
Construction

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC 2006 classification in Division E (Construction) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "30" to "32". The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classification and code range was Division E 4100 - 4299.
Div DJHMNP

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC 2006 classification in Division D (Electricity, Gas, Water, Waste), J (Information, Media and Telecommunications), H (Accommodation and Food Services), M (Professional, Scientific or Technical Services), P (Education and Training) or N (Administrative and Support Services) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "26" to "29" , "44" , "45" , "54" to "60", "69" to "73"or "80" to "83". The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classification and code range was Divisions D (Electricity, Gas and Water Supply) 3600 - 3799; Div H (Accommodation, Cafes and Restaurants) 5700 - 5799; Div J (Communication Services) 7100 - 7199; Div N (Education) 8400 - 8499.
Finance Insurance

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC classification in Division K (Finance and Insurance) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "62" to "64". The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classification and code range was Division K 7300 - 7599.
Health

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC 2006 classification in Division Q (Health Care and Social Assistance) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "84" to "87". The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classification and code range was Division O (Health and Community Services) 8600 - 8799.
Manufacturing

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC 2006 classification in Division C (Manufacturing) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "11" to "25". The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classification and code range was Division C 2100 - 2999.
Mining

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC 2006 classification in Division B (Mining) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "06" to "10". The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classification and code range was Division B 1100 - 1599.
Other ARF395

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC 2006 classification that is in Division D, H, J, L, M, N, O, P, Q, R or S. The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classifications are Divisions D, H. J, L, M, N, O, P and Q.
Property Business Services

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC classification in Division L (Rental, Hiring and Real Estate Services) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "66" to "78". The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classification and code range was Division L (Property and Business Services) 7700 - 7899.
Public Admin Safety

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC 2006 classification in Division O (Public Administration and Safety) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "75" to "77". The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classification and code range was Division M (Government administration and Defence) 8100 - 8299.
Retail

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC 2006 classification in Division G (Retail Trade) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "39" to "43". The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classification and code range was Division G 5100 - 5399.
Transport Post Warehousing

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC 2006 classification in Division I (Transport, Postal and Warehousing) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "46" to "53". The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classification and code range was Division I (Transport and Storage) 6100 - 6799.
Wholesale

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC 2006 classification in Division F (Wholesale Trade) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "33" to "38". The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classification and code range was Division F 4500 - 4799.
Wholesale Retail Transport

The counterparty in relation to the reported information has an ANZSIC 2006 classification in either:
- Division F (Wholesale Trade) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "33" to "38"; or
- Division G (Retail Trade) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "39" to "43"; or
- Division I (Transport, Postal and Warehousing) - i.e. its ANZSIC code commences with the digits "46" to "53".
The equivalent ANZSIC 1993 classifications and code ranges were Division F (4500 - 4799), Division G 5100 - 5399 and Division I (Transport and Storage) 6100 - 6799.
